	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Suggestions for EQ, Gordon replies...</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=90081" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top">
		    <p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    Three detailed posts here by Gordon replying to some player suggestions. First up Gordon responds to a NODROP item idea, second is solution to Dual Weilding Pets, and lastly a Solo'able only zone... Gordon's comments in Bold.
<Blockquote>
Let's take care of e-bay....let's take care of farming. Let's have the people who camp for a item actually need it or be there to help a friend or guildmate. What's that you say? Making most items no drop means you cannot trade for something else? TOUGH! Go earn it yourself then. If your only argument is going to be that you cannot trade for items you may need...That is a poor excuse. I much rather see people camping something cause THEY need the item, not because they sell it on E-bay or trade it so they can obtain something else that they could go camp at another time. Another argument might be that it is bad for the economy. What economy? Everyone trades items. What good is plat? Have way too much plat? Go support your local shaman figure out Alchemy. As far as I am conerned, making most items NO DROP will eliminate the farming of items and make them more attainable for everyone. <P>

<B>I think we'll see more new items become NODROP as the game progresses. NODROP solves a lot of problems, but also creates some others. Given the choice, I'd rather see the "Lore for Life" tag that was suggested by a few people a while ago. We brought that up and unfortuneatly it's not something that could go in. At least not without a Pwipe, which I imagine would upset a few people :)<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

When someone casts a summoning spell, it spawns a mob of the proper level. Some mobs in the game spawn with items on them. Can you have the Elementals automatically spawn with two weapons already equipped? Make the weapons of the appropriate delay for the elemental. Further, have the pet refuse to be given any other weapons (or at least not equip them).<P>

<B>We have the ability to make them spawn with weapons, but anything that can equip a weapon can be handed another weapon. The creature will then choose which weapon that it would rather equip based upon several factors. </B><P>

you could re-instate the low-delay buff for Necromancers and mobs.<P>

<B>Even if we were to make the change above, we wouldn't reinstate the delay speed bonus on the necromancer pets, as the investigation into the dual wield issue by the responsible coder led to the unavoidable conclusion that they (the necro pets) were too powerful. <P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

Create zones, both dungeons and outdoor zones that are geared toward the solo player. Make these zones off-limits to groups.. Make the Group function not even work within the zone. Fill it with monsters of low, medium and high levels that don't train easily and that DROP DECENT LOOT!<P>

<B>Being completely honest with you, this would be at odds with most of what EQ stands for. Since people in general have a tendency to follow the path of least resistance, everyone and their brother would be in these zones, and there'd be no way to control it. <P>

EQ is and will remain a group-oriented game, where people can choose a soloable class if they like. But though they'll be able to advance, they cannot expect to get the best items fighting exclusivly solo. <P>

-Gordon</B>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
		     <td valign="top">
		     <br><font face="Verdana" size="2"><b><a href="UserUpdate.asp?id=90081">[Add Comments] Please Add your comments here!</a></b></font><br><hr>
			  </td>
		</tr>

		</table>

	</td>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
</tr>
